<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
      xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal"
      xmlns:metal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/metal"
      metal:use-macro="base">

<tal:block metal:fill-slot="content">
    <div class="box large">
        <p>${request.session['filename']} was successfully converted. The converter attempts to preserve your content and formatting, but some formatting such as images, complex tables and formulae may not have imported correctly.</p>
        <p>You can check the preview below to see what your document looks like in cnxml.</p>
        <p>You can save a local copy of the converted file or click <b>next</b> if you are ready to save your document to your workspace on the server.</p>
        <a tal:attributes="href '%s%s/upload.zip' % (request.static_url('oerpub.rhaptoslabs.swordpushweb:transforms/'), request.session['upload_dir'])">Save a local copy</a>
        <a href="/metadata" class="large" style="float:right;">Next</a>
    </div>
    <iframe src="" tal:attributes="src '%s%s/' % (request.static_url('oerpub.rhaptoslabs.swordpushweb:transforms/'), request.session['upload_dir'])" frameborder="1" width="99%" height="800"></iframe>
</tal:block>
</html>
